node.text:
For anybody who’s been wondering what our brand @newyorkornowhere is all about, I’m excited to share a behind-the-scenes look at the making of our upcoming capsule collection, “Idlewild,” which was designed in collaboration with @AmericanExpress for their inaugural Membership Week celebration.

My co-founder @quincymoore takes the lead this time around to give you an inside peek at how this project came to life right here in New York City. Check out @newyorkornowhere's IG stories to see how the collection is coming together through collaborative design with Amex and NYON social media followers, and unveiled live tomorrow Friday, June 18th.

Thank you for all of your love & support this past year. We can't wait for you to see (and help with) this collection. And remember -  Amex can take you anywhere, but it will always be #newyorkornowhere.

Please take five minutes to watch “A Week in June,” an incredible documentary short by @jaysansone. Filmed around NYC over the past few weeks, Jay follows three young leaders in the #blacklivesmatter movement as part of an open discussion surrounding police violence and protesting. While some might call protestors “agitators,” “troublemakers,” or even “criminals,” Jay found impassioned human beings, whose passion for justice and reforming our beleaguered policing system was nothing short of inspirational. We’re honored to be premiering this film; a raw, real life look -- captured in the moment from the streets of New York City -- at a seminal week in human history.⁣
⁣
⁣
#blacklivesmatter #newyorktogether

Our heroes. ⁣
⁣
The coronavirus is the largest collective struggle of many of our lives. It is era and world defining.⁣
⁣
Yet, without minimizing the psychological, political, and economical impacts of the virus, the vast majority of us have one very simple, very helpful task: stay home. ⁣
⁣
Just stay home.⁣
⁣
The medical workers in our communities are putting their lives on the line, day and night, for our collective wellbeing. They are carrying the torch forth.⁣
⁣
So, let's thank them by doing what they can't: staying home.⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
Special thanks to all the heroic healthcare workers who participated in the making of this film and the office of @nygovcuomo for your support and collaboration 🙏⁣

node.text:
We can feel New York's soul through our apartment walls: it's the sound of our downstairs neighbor singing, of our upstairs neighbor dragging chairs across the floor. It's the smell of our neighbor's cooking wafting under the door, the sight of the policemen on the streets. It's all of us--at one in our isolation, closer for our apartness--getting through this, together.⁣
⁣
New York may be the home of tough love, but we need your help. If you can please reach out to the New York Governor's office @nygovcuomo at COVID19supplies@esd.ny.gov to donate masks and medical supplies to our frontline health workers.⁣
⁣
We would like to thank everyone involved for their contribution to this film. It is a privilege to film this city we all love ❤️🗽.⁣
⁣
⁣
#nytough #newyorktough #convicts #nyc #newyork #newyorkcity #newyorktogether ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
Film credits:⁣
Thank you to @convicts for this incredibly moving video. 
Andrew Clancy @andyclancy⁣
Matthew Kraus @matthewkrausphotography⁣
Lukas Willasch @lukaswillasch⁣

Amberly Kamroft & Florent Piovesan @oftwolands⁣

node.text: A few snaps from my special staycation at the @boweryhotel. My nearly two week stay (🤪) was filled with one too many room service orders of cacio e pepe and aperol spritzs from @gemma_ristorante, sunset drinks with friends in the garden and playing morning fetch with Charlie out on the patio. Thank you to @popeofthebowery for endlessly spoiling me while I was here; the incredibly warm and wonderful staff made us feel so at home. I’ll be back soon…🥰

node.text: As a New Yorker and hospitality professional, Leo Jacob aka @popeofthebowery was pretty annoyed with those pushing the narrative that “NYC is dead”, so he did something about it. Equipped with @leicacamerausa’s in hand, he interviewed and photographed many of the people that operated our most beloved restaurants amidst the harsh restrictions, health & financial concerns due to COVID. New York icons such as Mario Carbone, Maya Jankelowitz, Sean MacPherson, Donna Lennard, Jennifer Saesue, Justin Sievers, Karim Raoul and many more are featured in his book titled “NEW YORK IS DEAD? LONG LIVE NEW YORK!”, which is now available for pre-order. #newyorkornowhere #popeofthebowery

node.text: After walking through my empty apartment one last time, I looked over and saw my sweet pup Charlie just sitting there, knowing that these were the last few moments we’d have in the place that I welcomed him into. ❤️ My little sidekick and I are hotel hopping until I move into my new apartment in mid-August, much like a downtown version of Eloise and Weenie (IYKYK). 👧🏻🐶

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by New York City by Liz Eswein in Manhattan, New York with @roadwaymoving. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
As New Yorkers, our apartments didn’t used to be places where we spent a lot of time, functioning mostly as somewhere to eat meals and rest our heads in-between the hustle and bustle of daily life. 

Then 2020 happened and our homes took on new and different meanings… safe havens, work spaces, and environments that suddenly became the center of our world and social experiences. 

A lot of my best memories from the past year are tied to my abode on the Lower East Side. It was the first time I had enough time to really make that apartment feel like home. 

Next month I’m starting my next chapter in a new spot just a neighborhood or two away, and I’m very thankful to the fine folks @roadwaymoving who’ve helped make my move a breeze. #newyorkornowhere

node.text:
Meet Crystal, a #proud LGBTQ+ New Yorker “grateful to those who have taken the time to help [her]”, including @aliforneycenter, the nation’s largest organization dedicated to homeless LGBTQ+ youth. Crystal is rocking pieces from the Pride-inspired @newyorkornowhere “Confetti” Capsule, with a portion of proceeds going to support the life saving work of The Ali Forney Center. 🎉🌈

#nycpride #loveislove #pridemonth #lovewins
